dership.  “If there’s no other alternative,” he added, “It’s up to this president.” Garcado’s decision means the fate of Cuba’s two U.S. foreign missions will be decided by the Cuban Congress. Cuba has already declared that Garcado’s actions “totally nullified” the U.S. approval of Cuban construction projects for Havana that began under Raul and President Fidel Castro. Garcado has said he
